sqldk runs sql statements against R data frames using the duckdb database.
The dk in the name stands for duckdb.

There is a single user accessible function, sqldk.  It is usually called with
a single argument which is a character string or vector specifying SQL
statement(s).  For example,

  library(sqldk)
  DF <- data.frame(a = 1:3, b = 4:6)
  sqldk("select a, b, a + b as c from DF where a > 1")

For more information:

- from the R console: 
    ?"package-sqldk"
    ?sqldk

- from WWW
    https://github.com/ggrothendieck/sqldk
    https://duckdb.org/docs
    https://R.duckdb.org

For installation instructions see the INSTALL file.

